I once wrote about a Vietnamese man who escaped from a &quot;re-education&quot; camp to escape via Cambodia. In doing so, he lost part of his family. The story is on one of these threads. I wrote that I didn't make up the story, that I didn't have to, because these stories were all around us. All we had to do was to listen.<br><br>
I really believe that what needs to be done to counter these misperceptions of the Vietnamese, is for these stories to be told by those in the Vietnamese communities. If in black and white, it is awfully hard to ignore. Viet Son, I invite you to tell your stories, in part, or, in its entirety, so they cannot be ignored. Nobody can listen if nothing is said. This is your forum, your soapbox!
